her among the small group of Connecticut Hooker descendants who carried New Haven Colony founding-family ancestry alongside their Hartford-Hooker line. The combined Eaton-Hooker descent represented the merger of the two principal seventeenth-century Connecticut colonial-founder lineages."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Named for aunt Mabel Stiles Frost","body":"Mabel was given the same first name as her maternal aunt Mabel Stiles Frost — the 'father of music at North Haven' Titus Frost's wife — preserving the family name across the Stiles-Eaton lines of the late-eighteenth-century North Haven community. Her grandmother Mabel Clark Stiles had been the original Mabel; the name passed through three generations of the family."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Baptized 1783 at St. John's Church North Haven","body":"Mabel was baptized in 1783 at St. John's Episcopal Church North Haven Connecticut. No birth date was recorded for her or for her siblings — the North Haven family's documentation for this generation depends on baptismal records rather than birth registers. Her death date is not documented in available sources."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","page":"Entry #1168"},{"short":"FamilySearch (KLB6-DH1)"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"mabel-eaton-1784"},"H01169":{"id":"H01169","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Abigail","last_name":"Eaton","married_names":[],"extra_names":["Heaton (FamilySearch variant; corruption of Eaton)"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Abigail Eaton"},"birth":{"year":1786,"city":"North Haven","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{"year":1786,"city":"North Haven","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"death":{},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_sp